timeline.bodyText:
It's important to only send this thread's new reported property. If it sends the device's full reported property set, then iothub will receive two twin messages. one with:
{
  "key1":"oldValue1",
  "key2":"someUpdatedValue2"
}

and another with
{
  "key1":"someUpdatedValue1",
  "key2":"someUpdatedValue2"
}

but iothub may process them out of order, and the resulting twin representation on the service side could be either
{
  "key1":"someUpdatedValue1",
  "key2":"someUpdatedValue2"
}

or the incorrect representation
{
  "key1":"oldValue1",
  "key2":"someUpdatedValue2"
}

