replies.bodyText:
The test would fail in the latter case because it was expecting a final state of
{
  "key1":"someUpdatedValue1",
  "key2":"someUpdatedValue2"
}

So the fix here is to just send one property at a time, as it gets updated.
{
  "key1":"someUpdatedValue1"
}

and
{
  "key2":"someUpdatedValue2"
}

so that iothub's representation of this twin will always be
{
  "key1":"someUpdatedValue1",
  "key2":"someUpdatedValue2"
}

